CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Vets Capture La Salle - Thirteen men and one woman swapped Army drab for white caps and gowns as they received diplomas from La Salle July 26. Graduates include, left to right, front row; Harold K. Shelton, Cornelia D. Warfield, second row; Douglas Davis, James Primons Jr., and Louis K. Jones, third row; Arthur M. Frasier, George F. Brooks, and Clarence L. McCraw, fourth row; Willie B. Julks, Joseph W. Higgins, and Seamon Richards, fifth row; Charles Jordan, and Albert McWhite. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: La Salle graduates, front row from left: Harold K. Shelton, Cornelia D. Warfield; second row: Douglas Davis, James Primons Jr., Louis K. Jones; third row: Arthur M. Frasier, George F. Brooks, Clarence L. McCraw; fourth row: Willie B. Julks, Joseph W. Higgins, Seamon Richards; fifth row: Charles Jordan, Albert McWhite, and unknown, standing on stairs
